Dear families,
I would like to take this time to ‚ÄúThank you‚Äù for such an amazing start to the school year. Your support and understanding as we respond to the unexpected invasion of COVID-19 has been exemplary. We truly appreciate the cooperation from all of our students for wearing their masks, without complaining, while in school. Also, thank you parents for adhering to our guidelines throughout this time of uncertainty. Thank you for taking the necessary steps to keep yourselves, your families, and our community healthy and safe.
Mr. Laboranti

post_text:
HAPPENING FRIDAY: We're joining schools across the state to Light Up the Stadium in a demonstration of solidarity during the COVID-19 pandemic.

On Friday, April 24th, starting at sunset, 8:30pm tentatively, the Whiting Warriors Athletic Field lights will be turned on for 25 minutes‚Äîone minute for each day students have been out of school. We want to recognize our high school seniors whose last few months of high school have been changed by the pandemic.

It's part of the Iowa High School Athletic Directors Association's #BetheLightIA initiative, which kicked off last week.

We encourage our community members to drive, bike or walk by the stadium on Friday evening, as long as we all follow social distancing guidelines. We look forward to lighting up the Whiting Warriors Athletic Fields and showing our support!

January 6 at 10:19 AM ¬∑

Coaching Application

Are you interested or know someone interested in coaching at Whiting? We have the following coaching positions opened:

- Head Baseball Coach
- Assistant Baseball Coach
- Assistant Track Coach
- Assistant Volleyball Coach

Anyone interested may pick up an application at the school located at 606 West St. in Whiting, IA, or may fill out the online application found at TeachIowa.gov, or at our school website. We will need proof of coaching endorsement, 3 references as well as any other pertinent information. You may call Alex Lamp, AD with any questions at 712-455-2468 or email alamp@whitingcsd.org. All positions are opened until filled.

Whiting Warriors Athletics & Activities
October 9, 2019 at 8:39 PM ¬∑

All the hard work the past two months is starting to pay off for the Cross Country team! The Conference Meet was held today, and the team walked away with hardware! The girls took 3rd place. Leading the way for the Lady Warriors was Halle Murray, finishing in 5th. Not too far behind was Trinity McClure in 7th! The boys team takes 2nd overall! Leading the way for them was Austin Warren in 8th place. Atley Nelson & Lance Nichols followed him finishing 9th & 10th respectively! Great job Warriors!
